of
rock
that
rose
from
the
water
like
the
pillars
of
some
sea
godвЂ™s
temple,
while
the
angry
waves
foamed
and
crashed
among
them.

Drear,
dark,
forbidding,
Pyke
stood
atop
those
islands
and
pillars,
almost
a
part
of
them,
its
curtain
wall
closing
off
the
headland
around
the
foot
of
the
great
stone
bridge
that
leapt
from
the
clifftop
to
the
largest
islet,
dominated
by
the
massive
bulk
of
the
Great
Keep.
Farther
out
were
the
Kitchen
Keep
and
the
Bloody
Keep,
each
on
its
own
island.
Towers
and
outbuildings
clung
to
