the
gate
shuddered
and
the
snake
clanked
and
slithered
and
held.
Through
the
bars
he
could
look
down
the
long
stone
burrow
that
ran
between
the
walls
to
the
stony
field
beyond,
but
there
was
no
way
through.
He
could
force
his
muzzle
between
the
bars,
but
no
more.
Many
a
time
his
brother
had
tried
to
crack
the
black
bones
of
the
gate
between
his
teeth,
but
they
would
not
